This week's One Good Thing is a surprising laundry tip that comes from one of Maxwell's friends in the theater business — since they have so many opportunities to put on the same costumes, but need to remove those annoying odors that get caught over time. Vodka, it turns out, is a perfect odor remover as it is odorless and colorless itself! 

Read more at the link in bio. #OneGoodThingAtHome

node.title: Why You Should Keep Vodka With Your Clothes

node.text:
Almost every piece was replaced in homeowner @arianna_danielson’s glam, eclectic bathroom redo — except, that is, the vanity. Since it was in solid shape, Arianna didn’t want to scrap it. Instead, she and her husband crafted new doors with a textured wood style and oversized gold pulls, then painted them in fresh periwinkle paint. The project saved money and materials — and the vanity’s completely unrecognizable now. For more of the best before & after makeovers we saw this past month, head to the link in bio.
